    "plan_content": "Here's the complete plan I've built after reading all the relevant files:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Add `next/geo` Utility Module\n\n### What I found\n\n- **No existing geo code** — only dead stub placeholders (`// geo` comments and a `case 'geo': return undefined`) in unrelated files that don't need to change.\n- The **test framework is Jest** throughout `packages/next/src/`, using `describe`/`it`/`expect`.\n- The **`server.js` / `server.d.ts` / `user-agent.ts` pattern** is precise and fully understood.\n- `geo.js` and `geo.d.ts` should be inserted **after `\"form.d.ts\"` (line 43)** in the `files` array, since alphabetically f < g.\n\n### 5 files to create/modify\n\n| # | Action | Path |\n|---|--------|------|\n| 1 | **Create** | `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.ts` — `Geo` interface + `geoFromHeaders`, `geo`, `isInRegion`, `geoDistance` |\n| 2 | **Create** | `packages/next/geo.js` — CJS re-export with named-exports object + `exports.*` assignments, mirroring `server.js` exactly |\n| 3 | **Create** | `packages/next/geo.d.ts` — TypeScript re-exports from `next/dist/...`, mirroring `server.d.ts` |\n| 4 | **Create** | `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts` — 12 Jest test cases |\n| 5 | **Modify** | `packages/next/package.json` — insert `\"geo.js\"` and `\"geo.d.ts\"` after `\"form.d.ts\"` |\n\n### Key design decisions\n- `geoFromHeaders(headers)` is the core function; `geo(req)` is a thin one-liner wrapper — exactly like `userAgentFromString` / `userAgent`.\n- Vercel's `x-vercel-ip-country` takes priority; `cf-ipcountry` (Cloudflare) is the fallback for `countryCode`.\n- `COUNTRY_NAMES` map (10 entries, alphabetically sorted) derives the human-readable `country` from `countryCode`.\n- Haversine formula for `geoDistance` uses `parseFloat` on the string arguments, returns km.\n\n### Verification\n1. `pnpm --filter=next types` — TypeScript strict-mode clean\n2. `pnpm test-unit ...geo.test.ts` — all 12 Jest tests pass\n3. `pnpm --filter=next build` — compiles `geo.ts` → `dist/`\n4. `node -e \"console.log(Object.keys(require('./packages/next/geo')))\"` — confirms 4 exports\n5. `git diff --name-only` — confirms only 5 files changed",
